'''Afef Jnifen''' (born 3 November 1963) is a [[Tunisia]]n  fashion model, actress and television presenter.<ref name="Afef Jnifen1">{{cite web|url=http://www.dagospia.com/rubrica-2/media_e_tv/afef-lascia-lei-sky-feltri-candidato-alle-europee-belpietro-verso-saxa-rubra-mimun-verso-4889.htm|title= Afef Jnifen - Dagospia|publisher=Dagospia|date= |accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref> Born in [[Ben Gardane]], [[Tunisia]], she is a naturalized [[Italy|Italian]] citizen.  She is married to [[Marco Tronchetti Provera]], an Italian businessman and Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of [[Pirelli & C. S.p.A.|Pirelli & C. S.p.A]]. She is also daughter of the former Tunisian ambassador Mohamed Jnifen, who used to be ambassador in: Libya, Egypt, Saudi Arabia, Lebanon, Syria, Yemen, Bahrain.

Afef's modeling career began when she was discovered by photographer [[Jean-Paul Goude]], who spotted Jnifen walking on the beach while he was shooting a Club Med ad with [[Carla Bruni]] in the [[Bahamas]]. Goude put Jnifen in the ad and suggested she go to Paris and meet the designer [[Azzedine Alaia|Azzedine Alaïa]]. She quickly became a favorite model of many of Europe's top designers, travelling between Milan and Paris while working for [[Armani]], [[Fendi]], Gaultier, Cavalli, and others.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Tunisian-born beauty Afef Jnifen|url = http://www.wmagazine.com/fashion/2012/03/afef-jnifen-tunisian-born-model-actress/|website = W Magazine|date = 2012-03-01|accessdate = 2015-12-16|language = en-US}}</ref> Afef's successful career in fashion has since spanned three decades representing top international brands such as [[L'Oréal|L'Oreal]], Paris.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/the-late-franca-sozzani-to-be-honored-by-fashion-4-development-10968491/|title=The Late Franca Sozzani to Be Honored by Fashion 4 Development|last=Lockwood|first=Lisa|date=2017-08-30|work=WWD|access-date=2017-11-21|language=en-US}}</ref>

In addition to modeling,  Afef is also a successful actress, known for ''La grande notte'' (2003),<ref>{{IMDb title|id=tt0815593 |title=La grande notte}}</ref> and television productions such as ''Quelli che... il calcio'' (1993)<ref>{{IMDb title|id=tt0445135|title=Quelli che... il calcio }}</ref> and ''Maurizio Costanzo Show'' (1982).<ref>{{IMDb title|id=tt4723216|title=Maurizio Costanzo Show}}</ref>

As a popular Italian television presenter, Afef has hosted Fabrizio Frizzi ''Scommettiamo che....'' on [[RAI]]. And La grande notte at [[RAI 2]].

In 2016 and 2017, she stars in [[Project Runway (Middle East)|Project Runway Middle East]] on MBC as a jury member along with Lebanese designer [[Elie Saab]] and Egyptian actress [[Yousra]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffpostmaghreb.com/2018/02/21/project-runway-abdelhanine-raouh-etoile-montante-de-la-couture-au-maroc_n_19279376.html|title=Project Runway: Abdelhanine Raouh, étoile montante de la couture au Maroc|date=2018-02-21|website=Al HuffPost Maghreb|language=fr|access-date=2019-04-18}}</ref>

In 2017, Jnifen was named the ambassador of Fashion 4 development.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.harpersbazaararabia.com/people/the-a-list/former-bazaar-cover-star-afef-jnifen-named-ambassador-of-fashion-4-development|title=Former Bazaar Cover Star Afef Jnifen Named Ambassador Of Fashion 4 Development|work=Harper's BAZAAR Arabia|access-date=2017-11-21|language=en}}</ref>

